 X（前身为 Twitter）停止显示新闻报道标题——用户反应https://www.nme.com/news/music/x-known-twitter-stops-showing-news-story-headlines-users-react-3509798?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=x-known-twitter-stops-显示新闻故事标题用户反应Tom SkinnerThu, 05 Oct 2023 10:39:32 +0000 Music NewsNewsElon MuskTwitter https://www.nme.com/?p=3509798 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="官方 X（以前称为 Twitter）徽标" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>埃隆·马斯克对该网站最新的有争议的更改于昨天（10 月 4 日）上线</p><p>Post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/x-formerly-twitter-stops-showing-news-story-headlines-users-react-3509798">X（以前称为 Twitter）停止显示新闻报道标题 – 用户反应</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="官方 X（以前称为 Twitter）徽标" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Twitter-X-logo-headlines-story-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> X（以前称为<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/twitter">Twitter</a> ）已停止在该平台上向某些用户显示新闻报道标题。</p><p>该社交媒体网站（<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/elon-musk-completes-twitter-takeover-3338149">埃隆·马斯克去年斥资 440 亿美元收购</a>）目前仅显示文章中包含的主图片，以及左下角发布该文章的网站的链接。</p><p>在此最新更新之前，用户能够在提供有关相关文章的更多信息的简短描述上方看到完整的标题（或针对社交媒体改编的标题）。这些被称为“ <a href="https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/twitter-for-websites/cards/overview/abouts-cards" target="_blank" rel="noopener">卡片</a>”。</p><p>该更改于昨天（10 月 4 日星期三）对 iOS 和桌面用户生效。 According to <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/oct/05/x-twitter-strips-headlines-new-links-why-elon-musk" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Guardian</em></a> , the new appearance does not apply to advertisement links on X.</p><p> The plan to remove headlines had been in the works since August. Following the initial reports about the update, Musk <a href="https://x.com/elonmusk/status/1693843680904216619?s=20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tweeted</a> : “This is coming from me directly. Will greatly improve the esthetics.”</p><p> He <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1693756240260698550" target="_blank" rel="noopener">said</a> earlier: “If you&#39;re a journalist who wants more freedom to write and a higher income, then publish directly on this platform!”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> This is coming from me directly. Will greatly improve the esthetics.</p><p> — Elon Musk (@elonmusk) <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1693843680904216619?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">August 22, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Recent <a href="https://digiday.com/media/publishers-lament-the-removal-of-twitter-moments-as-referral-traffic-dips/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">reports</a> indicate that traffic for media publishers has declined from X/Twitter since Musk&#39;s takeover, which has seen the tech billionaire make a range of controversial changes.</p><p> It is said that X/Twitter briefly put a five-second delay on loading links to online news outlets and rivals to the site including <em>Reuters</em> , <em>The New York Times</em> and Instagram over the summer.</p><p> On Tuesday (October 3) Musk <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1709249243196580323" target="_blank" rel="noopener">posted</a> : “I almost never read legacy news anymore. What&#39;s the point of reading 1000 words about something that was already posted on X several days ago?”</p><p> He explained in a separate <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1709244708533264592" target="_blank" rel="noopener">update</a> : “Our algorithm tries to optimize time spent on X, so links don&#39;t get as much attention, because there is less time spent if people click away.</p><p> “Best thing is to post content in long form on this platform.”</p><p> The move could be an attempt to persuade people to sign up for X Premium, which allows subscribers to post up to 25,000 characters and access a range of other advantages. With the removal of headlines, users may need to include more text to accompany their posts.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Interesting.</p><p> Our algorithm tries to optimize time spent on X, so links don&#39;t get as much attention, because there is less time spent if people click away.</p><p> Best thing is to post content in long form on this platform.</p><p> — Elon Musk (@elonmusk) <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1709244708533264592?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">October 3, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Following the scrapping of headlines, Musk shared a <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1709475380715823349" target="_blank" rel="noopener">post</a> in which he said he believes “citizen journalism is the path to [a] better future”, adding: “I strongly encourage people around the world to post news about events as they&#39;re happening, in both text &amp; video.”</p><p> Numerous media figures have since criticised Musk&#39;s latest adaptation to the feed. Tom Warren, Senior Editor at <em>The Verge</em> , wrote: “You can no longer see the headlines of articles linked on Twitter (X) anymore.</p><p> “It&#39;s just an image. It&#39;s the latest in a long line of dumb changes on this platform.”</p><p> <em>PC Gamer</em> , meanwhile, highlighted a series of its posts that appeared without context due to their missing headlines. “Here&#39;s a few of our gems/victims of the new change,” the caption to the humorous screenshots read.</p><p> Steve Boxer, a gaming writer for <em>The Guardian</em> , said: “Didn&#39;t realise that Musk&#39;s new Twitter is already stripping out headlines in links to articles. What a shit-show. Will have to add them manually from now on.”</p><p> Another person commented: “Musk seems determined to make Twitter a less useful, a less usable, and a less pleasant place to be. Latest is the removal of headlines from linked posts.</p><p> “Dreadful move. He&#39;s confusing minutes spent doom scrolling with utility/value. It&#39;s not.”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> you can no longer see the headlines of articles linked on Twitter (X) anymore. It&#39;s just an image. It&#39;s the latest in a long line of dumb changes on this platform <a href="https://t.co/ii20NIZXrk">https://t.co/ii20NIZXrk</a></p><p> — Tom Warren (@tomwarren) <a href="https://twitter.com/tomwarren/status/1709712891379675192?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">October