 Vinyl sales up nearly 15 per cent in 2023 https://www.nme.com/news/music/vinyl-sales-up-nearly-15-per-cent-in-2023-3509810?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=vinyl-sales-up-nearly-15-per-cent-in-2023Liberty Dunworth Thu, 05 Oct 2023 10:14:48 +0000 Music NewsNewsVinyl https://www.nme.com/?p=3509810 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Vinyl record stock photo" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Albums from Taylor Swift, Blur and Lana Del Rey are among the best-selling</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/vinyl-sales-up-nearly-15-per-cent-in-2023-3509810">Vinyl sales up nearly 15 per cent in 2023</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Vinyl record stock photo" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Sales of vinyl have surged by nearly 15 per cent year-on-year for the first nine months of 2023, according to a new report.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/whats-causing-the-vinyl-delay-adele-is-not-the-problem-say-music-industry-insiders-3094213">What&#39;s causing the vinyl delay? “Adele is not the problem”, say music industry insiders</a></strong></li></ul><p> The statistics were collected from the BPI (via <a href="https://www.musicweek.com/labels/read/vinyl-sales-surge-13-2-in-2023-ahead-of-black-friday-and-blockbuster-q4/088617" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>MusicWeek</em></a> ) and highlighted that from the beginning of the year until the end of September, 3,952,262 vinyl LPs were sold – approximately a 13.2 per cent increase since 2022.</p><p> According to the report, this increase was even bigger for the three months of the Q3 period, which saw 1,237,620 records sold in the vinyl format; a figure which is 15.1 per cent higher than the previous year.</p><p> So far, artists majorly responsible for the resurgence of vinyl sales include <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lana-del-rey">Lana Del Rey</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/taylor-swift">Taylor Swift</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/blur">Blur</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kylie-minogue">Kylie Minogue</a> – all of which have released new LPs since the start of the year.</p><p> So far, Lana Del Rey&#39;s &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/lana-del-rey-did-you-know-that-theres-a-tunnel-under-ocean-blvd-review-3415497">Did You Know That There&#39;s A Tunnel Under Ocean Blvd</a> &#39; remains the biggest vinyl release of the year – with 33,568 copies sold on the format since its release in March. This is followed by Taylor Swift&#39;s &#39;Speak Now (Taylor&#39;s Version)&#39;, which was the biggest-selling vinyl release of Q3, with 29,649 sales.</p><p> In third place is Britpop icons Blur, whose ninth studio album &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/blur-the-ballad-of-darren-review-lyrics-tracklist-3470424">The Ballad Of Darren</a> &#39; has sold 26,894 copies, and Kylie Minogue&#39;s &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/kylie-minogue-tension-review-lyrics-tracklist-3501195">Tension</a> &#39; isn&#39;t too far behind, with 19,160 copies sold since its release last month. </p><figure id="attachment_3509821" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3509821" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3509821" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Taylor-Swift@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Taylor Swift performs during The Eras Tour 2023" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Taylor-Swift@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Taylor-Swift@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Taylor-Swift@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Taylor-Swift@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Taylor-Swift@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Taylor-Swift@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3509821" class="wp-caption-text"> Taylor Swift performs during The Eras Tour 2023. CREDIT: Allen J. Schaben/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> Other albums paving the way in vinyl sales include <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/olivia-rodrigo">Olivia Rodrigo</a> &#39;s &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/olivia-rodrigo-guts-album-review-vampire-3493907">Guts</a> &#39;, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/wham">Wham!</a> &#39;s &#39;The Singles: Echoes From The Edge Of Heaven&#39; and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lewis-capaldi">Lewis Capaldi</a> &#39;s &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/lewis-capaldi-broken-by-desire-to-be-heavenly-sent-review-3444656">Broken By Desire To Be Heavenly Sent</a> &#39;.</p><p> What&#39;s more, this figure is expected to rise significantly for the remainder of 2023, with albums from <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/take-that">Take That</a> (&#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/take-that-return-announce-new-album-and-announce-massive-uk-and-ireland-stadium-tour-pre-order-buy-tickets-3502377">This Life</a> &#39;) and Taylor Swift (&#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/streams-of-taylor-swifts-1989-double-after-re-recording-announcement-3483064">1989 (Taylor&#39;s Version)</a> &#39;) still set for release. Another artist set to make a huge mark on the figures this year is rock icons <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-rolling-stones">The Rolling Stones</a> , who will be sharing &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">Hackney Diamonds</a> &#39; – their first new album of original music in 18 years on October 20.</p><p> The number is also set to be inflated with Black Friday – Record Store Day&#39;s sister event – on the horizon (November 24). This will see limited edition vinyl editions released for over 90 artists, including <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/joni-mitchell">Joni Mitchell</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/prince">Prince</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-doors">The Doors</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/post-malone">Post Malone</a> . </p><figure id="attachment_3509823" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3509823" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3509823" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock-photo@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Music vinyl record collection retro vintage style - stock photo" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock-photo@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock-photo@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock-photo@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock-photo@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock-photo@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Vinyl-stock-photo@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3509823" class="wp-caption-text"> Music vinyl record collection retro vintage style – stock photo. CREDIT: Kelly Bowden/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> As reported by <em>MusicWeek</em> , CD sales for 2023 have dropped by 6.3 per cent year-on-year, and physical sales as a whole are down by 0.5 per cent. Unsurprisingly, streaming continues to be the main way music is being consumed, making up 88.5 per cent of the market.</p><p> In other vinyl news, back in August it was reported that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/scotlands-first-ever-vinyl-pressing-plant-is-under-construction-3487364">Scotland&#39;s first-ever vinyl-pressing plant was under construction – set to open later this year</a> .</p><p> Named Seabass Vinyl, is the family-run business of David and Dominique Harvey, and is set to open its doors in East Lothian, just outside Edinburgh, later this month.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/vinyl-sales-up-nearly-15-per-cent-in-2023-3509810">Vinyl sales up nearly 15 per cent in 2023</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
