 “general bug fixes and improvements”. </p><figure id="attachment_3480534" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3480534" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3480534" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/red-dead-redemption-film-is-extremely-unlikely.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/red-dead-redemption-film-is-extremely-unlikely.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/red-dead-redemption-film-is-extremely-unlikely-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/red-dead-redemption-film-is-extremely-unlikely-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/red-dead-redemption-film-is-extremely-unlikely-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/red-dead-redemption-film-is-extremely-unlikely-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/red-dead-redemption-film-is-extremely-unlikely-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3480534" class="wp-caption-text"> &#39;Red Dead Redemption&#39; Credit: Take-Two Interactive</figcaption></figure><p> Back in August, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/red-dead-redemption-publisher-defends-re-releases-controversial-price-3480337">Take-Two Interactive CEO Strauss Zelnick defended the decision to price <em>Red Dead Redemption</em> &#39;s port at £39.99</a> despite it making very few changes to the 13-year-old game.</p><p> “That&#39;s just what we believe is the commercially accurate price for it,” said Zelnick. He added that the <em>Undead Nightmare</em> expansion included in the port “was a great standalone game in its own right when it was originally released, so we feel like it&#39;s a great bundle for the first time, and certainly a great value for consumers”.</p><p> Meanwhile, Zelnick also said that TV or film adaptations of its games are “ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/red-dead-redemption-film-is-too-much-of-a-risk-suggests-publisher-3480504">probably a relatively small opportunity</a> ” for the company.</p><p> “We&#39;re not going to bet this company&#39;s future or the value of our intellectual property based on someone else&#39;s execution in another area of the entertainment business,” said Zelnick. He added that going forward, <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/take-two-interactive">Take-Two</a> will be “very selective” with potential adaptations of its games, which include the likes of <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/games/grand-theft-auto">Grand Theft Auto</a></em> and <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/games/mafia">Mafia</a></em> .</p><p> In other gaming news, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/diablo-4-is-on-its-way-to-steam-3509212"><em>Diablo 4</em> is coming to Steam later this month</a> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/red-dead-redemption-gets-60-fps-mode-on-ps5-3509723">&#39;Red Dead Redemption&#39; gets 60 FPS mode on PS5</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
